properties.Name: PolicyDeliveryMethod
properties.Description:
The means or vehicle by which policy and policy-related material/information is delivered to the Policyholder.

Ex:
- Constructive Delivery
- Inspection Receipt

CONSTRUCTIVE DELIVERY
Intentionally relinquishing control of a policy and turning over that control to someone acting for the Policyholder.

An example is when an insurer mails the policy to its own agent for delivery to the Policyholder.

Legally, an insurance policy is considered delivered when mailed or turned over to the Policyholder or someone acting on his or her behalf.

INSPECTION RECEIPT
A receipt obtained from an insurance applicant when a policy for which the first premium has not been paid is left with them for further inspection.

This receipt states that the insurance is not in effect and that the policy has been delivered for the purposes of inspection only.
